-- Russian Watchdog Approves 30 Billion Rubles of Severstal Bonds
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-07T17:01:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/russian-watchdog-approves-30-billion-rubles-of-severstal-bonds.html
OAO Severstal, billionaire Alexey Mordashov’s steelmaker, plans to sell 30 billion rubles ($951
million) of bonds, according to a statement by the Federal
Financial Market Service.  The watchdog said on its website it registered three
tranches of Severstal’s bonds of 15 billion rubles, 10 billion
rubles and 5 billion rubles respectively.  To contact the reporter on this story:
